-- Nasdaq CEO gets new contract and big option award
-- 
-- Fri Dec 15, 2006 6:07pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/15/us-nasdaq-ce0-contract-idUSWEN125620061215

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Nasdaq Stock Market Inc. ( NDAQ.O ) President and Chief Executive Robert Greifeld has received a new employment contract through 2010 and  an option award to buy nearly 1 million shares of the company's stock. 

 Greifeld, 49, joined Nasdaq in May 2003 and has led the stock exchange through an expansion that has included acquisitions of new trading platforms and a 29 percent stake in the London Stock Exchange. The company also disclosed that Greifeld received the right to buy 960,000 shares of company stock. The options, priced at $35.92 apiece, are exercisable in various installments through 2012, according to a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.